- and post-menopausal woman. With health education as a primary focus, this helps prevent problems and assist women in developing and maintaining good health habits throughout pregnancy and delivery[/service_box][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"][service_box icon=\"icon icon-shutterstock-166641992-converted-42\" title=\"Primary Care for Women\"]<span style=\"color: #444444;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, serif;\">We offer primary care services from colds to injuries, and more. We look at your personal health history, family history, laboratory analysis and physical examination to provide the</span></span>[/service_box][vc_empty_space height=\"30px\"][service_box icon=\"icon icon-shutterstock-166641992-converted-42\" title=\"Menopausal Care\"]<span style=\"color: #444444;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, serif;\">Menopause is a time in a woman\'s life when her period stops. This happens because the woman\'s ovary stops producing the hormones estrogen and progesterone</span></span><span style=\"color: #444444;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, serif;\"><b>. </b></span></span><span style=\"color: #444444;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, serif;\">This phase can occur between ages 45-55.</span></span>[/service_box][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"][service_box icon=\"icon icon-shutterstock-166641992-converted-42\" title=\"Gynecological Obstetrics\"]<span style=\"color: #444444;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, serif;\">We specialize in general women\'s medical care, diagnosis and treatment of disorders of the female reproductive system, and care of pregnant women. We recommend women who are either over 18 years of age, and/or are sexually active, or those who experience gynecological symptoms, have an annual gynecological exam. </span></span>[/service_box][vc_empty_space height=\"30px\"][service_box icon=\"icon icon-shutterstock-166641992-converted-42\" title=\"3D Ultrasounds\"]<span style=\"color: #444444;\"><span